{
  "texts": [
    "This is important because even though the regulatory authority is likely to be a trustworthy body, citizens will find it unpalatable to reveal their locations.",
    "Even if the citizen's queries anonymously reveal location, i.e., without disclosing the citizen's identity, prior work shows that citizens can be de-identified using historical query data (e.g., [76]).Pd-Mpc encodes the entire aforementioned geometric computation using the machinery of MPC, thereby ensuring the citizen's location privacy.",
    "In that sense, Privadome views the regulatory authority as an honest-but-curious participant.",
    "Delivery drone operators may also not wish to make the location of all their delivery drones publicly available to anybody that poses a query to the regulatory authority.",
    "Pd-Mpc has the pleasant side-effect of also ensuring this goal (to an extent), but this is a not our primary goal, whereas protecting citizen privacy is."
  ]
}